cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication systems and resource allocation, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses interference management and scheduling, which are topics related to information theory.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions multi-antenna base stations, which are commonly used in multimedia communication systems.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a method for handling interference in a wireless communication system, which can be seen as a control problem.
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the use of machine-type-devices in the system may raise security concerns, making this sub-category a possibility.
